title: Independent candidate Hamayun Khan wins PK-15 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Hamayun Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-15, Lower Dir-II by securing 31,346 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarian (PPPP) candidate Naeem Ullah who bagged 14,691 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 43.12 per cent.
